Prologue
"Please!" Queen Alvin pleaded, "Don't send her away! She's just a child!" Ice King sat on his throne, looking down at his wife, with the royal advisor standing beside him. The queen had given birth to a girl. Just thinking about it made the Ice King frown.
The infant looked like her mother: pale blue eyes, snow-white hair streaked with a few strands of blue. The Ice King thought giving birth to a daughter would make him seem weak. After all, up until then, he only had sons.
You have two choices, either kill this child or abandon her in the wilderness. Alvin, this is your punishment," he spat out her name as if it were poison, as he always did.
Frost Kingdom was not always a kingdom. It used to be divided into two parts, north and south. The northern part became a non-magical kingdom, while the southern part was a land of magical power. Due to the greed of the north, the two kingdoms waged endless war until peace was offered by the south.
#1 <s>At that time, the south was already hopeless, with the royal family willing to do anything to prevent this bloody conflict. They proposed marrying their only princess to the north to become the queen of the north, and to have a son as the future king. Afterward, the south would unite with the north to establish a unified kingdom. The north accepted this proposal, and Princess Alvin married Prince Akul.
#2 <s>“Please, my king, for the safety of my child, you can do anything to me. Lock me up, banish me, or even kill me.” Queen Alvin pleaded, hugging her child tightly.
#3 <s>The Ice King looked down at the queen with disgust in his eyes. Maybe, just maybe, he would have a shred of compassion for her. After all, this woman had been by his side for 22 years, caring for him when he was at his lowest, and giving birth to his children.
#4 <s>“Alright. The child can live in the palace.” Hearing the Ice King’s words, the queen sighed in relief. “But,” he added, “you will be executed.”
